Planetary ephemeris DE425 SPK, Short Version (1964-12-07 ... 2050-01-02)
============================================================================
 
   Created by William M. Folkner on 2012-05-04. Comments added by Boris
   Semenov on 2012-06-01.
 
   This SPK file was released on May 9, 2012 by the Solar System
   Dynamics (SSD) Group of JPL's Guidance, Navigation, and Control
   section for use by the Mars Science Laboratory (MSL) project.
 
   The DE425 planetary ephemeris is described in JPL IOM IOM 343R-12-002
   dated May 9, 2012. The introduction from that memo is provided
   below in Appendix 1. The full memo is available from SSD or NAIF
   upon request.
 
   The NIOSPK conversion log is provided in Appendix 2.
 
 
Appendix 1: Introduction from DE425 Release Memo (JPL IOM IOM 343R-12-002)
============================================================================
 
 
JET PROPULSION LABORATORY INTEROFFICE MEMORANDUM
IOM 343R-11-003
14 September 2011
 
     To:  Tomas Martin-Mur
   From:  W. M. Folkner
Subject:  Planetary ephemeris DE425 for Mars Science Laboratory arrival
 
1. Introduction
 
      The planetary ephemeris DE425 is an update to DE424 developed
   for MSL launch and early cruise (Folkner 2011). DE425 has been fit
   to the most recently available measurements of the position of Mars.
   Also, recent data for Venus and Mercury have been included. The
   change in the orbit estimates for Earth and Mars between DE424 and
   DE425 are small, less than 100 meters over the MSL cruise period and
   much less than the estimated uncertainty (Folkner 2010). The small
   change in Earth and Mars orbits is expected since the DE424 and
   DE425 data sets are largely the same and, starting with measurements
   available when DE424 was created, the VLBI data have improved such
   that the tie of the planetary ephemeris to the International
   Celestial Reference Frame (Fey et al. 2009) is now stable and
   accurate.
 
      DE425 is recommended for use by the Mars Science Laboratory
   mission. DE425 is also suitable for use by missions to other
   planets. DE425 was fit to a full set of planetary observations. The
   orbit of the Moon for DE425 is consistent with the orbit on DE421 at
   the meter level, while the lunar libration angles are consistent at
   the 0.01 arcsecond level, which is adequate for many purposes
   including MSL navigation. Use of DE421 is recommended for the most
   accurate lunar data analysis.
 
 
Appendix 2: Original NIOSPK Log
============================================================================
 
; de425s.bsp LOG FILE

    BEGIN_TIME      = CAL-ET 1964 DEC 07 00:00:00.000
    END_TIME        = CAL-ET 2050 JAN 02 00:00:00.000
 
; END NIOSPK COMMANDS
 
 
End of comments.

Ephemeris for Martian satellites from fit to all data.
Work is described in AJ 139 (2010) 668-679.
 
 THE ORBITS AND MASSES OF THE MARTIAN SATELLITES AND THE LIBRATION OF PHOBOS
 
                             R. A. Jacobson
        Jet Propulsion Laboratory, California Institute of Technology,
             4800 Oak Grove Drive, Pasadena, CA 91109-8099
                     robert.jacobson@jpl.nasa.gov
 
                              ABSTRACT
 
This paper reports on an update to the orbits and masses of the Martian
satellites, Phobos and Deimos.  We obtained the orbits by fitting a numerical
integration to all available Earthbased astrometry through the opposition of
2003, spacecraft imaging observations through 2007, and the Doppler tracking
of the Viking and Phobos 2 spacecraft; the Doppler data provide information
on the satellite masses.  Our dynamical model included the figure acceleration
due to a librating Phobos; we determined the amplitude of the forced libration.
We also took into account the secular acceleration of Phobos due to the tide
that it raises on Mars and estimated the Martian tidal quality factor Q.
We provide an assessment of the accuracy of the orbits and a geometrical
description of the orbits in the form of mean elements.

     GC (actual, 2012-08-08 solution) on the surface of Mars. The landing
     site NAIF ID and name are -76900 and 'MSL_LANDING_SITE'.

        Lat =  -4.643851 degrees North
        Alt =  -4.926878 km

                                     Ztr is into the page.

            b* are translations from the turret head to the tool reference
               point along the X axis of the tool frame.

               along the Z axis of the tool frame.
 
 
   Actual RA dimensions
   --------------------
 
      Relative positions between RA joints and tools with respect to
      appropriate frames can be "constructed" from a1..a5, d1..d5,
      x0..z0 and x1..z1, b1..b5, and c1..c5 shown on the diagrams above
      as follows:
 
         ----------------------------------------------------------------------
         Link#         X         Y        Z       CENTER/REF_FRAME
         ---------- --------- --------- --------- -----------------------------
         BASE        x0        y0        z0       ROVER/ROVER
         SH/AZ       x1        y1        z1       RA_BASE/RA_BASE
         SH/EL       a1        0.0       0.0      RA_SHOULDER_AZ/RA_SHOULDER_AZ
         ELBOW       a2        0.0       0.0      RA_SHOULDER_EL/RA_SHOULDER_EL
         WRIST       a3        0.0       0.0      RA_ELBOW/RA_ELBOW
         TURRET (a) -a4       -d5       -d4       RA_WRIST/RA_WRIST
         HEAD   (b)  0.0       0.0      -d6       RA_TURRET/RA_TURRET
         MAHLI_REF   b1        0.0       c1       RA_TURRET_HEAD/MAHLI_REF
         APXS_REF    b2        0.0       c2       RA_TURRET_HEAD/APXS_REF
         PADS_REF    b3        0.0       c3       RA_TURRET_HEAD/PADS_REF
         DRT_REF     b4        0.0       c4       RA_TURRET_HEAD/DRT_REF
         CHIMRA_REF  b5        0.0       c5       RA_TURRET_HEAD/CHIMRA_REF
         MAHLI  (c)  0.0       0.0       0.0      MAHLI_REF/MAHLI_REF
         APXS        0.0       0.0       0.0      APXS_REF/APXS_REF
         PADS        0.0       0.0       0.0      PADS_REF/PADS_REF
         DRT         0.0       0.0       0.0      DRT_REF/DRT_REF
         CHIMRA      0.0       0.0       0.0      CHIMRA_REF/CHIMRA_REF
         ----------------------------------------------------------------------
 
         (a) This translation combines translations from Wrist Joint (in [2])/
             ARM4 (in [1]) to Turret Joint (in [2])/ARM5 (in [1]) by elements
             a4 and d4 and from Turret Joint/ARM5 to Turret (in [2])/ARM6
             (in [1]) by element d5.
 
         (b) Turret head is called Tool Center in [2].
 
         (c) Location of MAHLI relative to MAHLI_REF is derived from the
             MAHLI CAHVORE model. Nominally it is set to (0,0,0).
 
      Same with the actual numbers from [1]:
 
         ----------------------------------------------------------------------
         Link#        X, m      Y, m      Z, m    CENTER/REF_FRAME
         ---------- --------- --------- --------- -----------------------------
         BASE       +0.82746  -0.561597 +0.224803 ROVER/ROVER
         SH/AZ      +0.285    +0.1095   +0.04101  RA_BASE/RA_BASE
         SH/EL      +0.155865  0.0       0.0      RA_SHOULDER_AZ/RA_SHOULDER_AZ
         ELBOW      +0.826258  0.0       0.0      RA_SHOULDER_EL/RA_SHOULDER_EL
         WRIST      +0.786501  0.0       0.0      RA_ELBOW/RA_ELBOW
         TURRET     -0.144429 -0.169434 -0.167437 RA_WRIST/RA_WRIST
         HEAD        0.0       0.0      -0.07176  RA_TURRET/RA_TURRET
         MAHLI_REF  +0.29826   0.0      -0.00998  RA_TURRET_HEAD/MAHLI_REF
         APXS_REF   +0.29904   0.0      -0.01024  RA_TURRET_HEAD/APXS_REF

HGA Point and Center Locations
===========================================================================
 
   References
   ----------
 
      1. FSW parameters, July 2012
 
      2. Drawing 10253071-C
 
 
   HGA Point and Center Locations Diagram
   --------------------------------------
 
      Rover -Y side view:
      -------------------
                                                   "point" X
                                     ->|--------|<----
                               _                   "center" X
                              | | RSM     ->|---|<----
                              `-'
                               |              HGA                |
                               |          .```.         .        v
                               |         |  o  -o-   .-' \ RTG  ---
          RA                   |     RM   `._.' | .-'     \      | "point" Z
      -|-                  |-.--------(*)--------'       .-     ---
       o---------o--------o| |                   |    .-'        ^
                             |.-------o----.     |-.-'           |
                           .-`--------------`-.--'
                           |             .-----`o------.
                         .-|-.         .-|-.         .-|-.
                        |  o  |       |  o  |       |  o  |
                         `._.'   <-------x.'         `._.'
                                Xr       |
                                         |
                                         |
                                      Zr v     Yr is into the page.
 
      Rover -Z side ("top") view:
      ---------------------------
 
                        .-----.       .-----.       .-----.
                        |     |       |     |       |     |
                        |     |       |             |     |
                        `--|--'       `-- Yr        `--|--'
                           `----------o- ^ -----o------'
                             ..-.------- | ------.     RTG
                         RSM || |        |       |--------.      |
                             || |        |       |-------.|      v
          RA                 |`- <----(*)x       |       ||     ---
       |                     |  Xr   RM      HGA |-------'|      | "point" Y
      -o---------|--------|o-|            ==o==-o---------'     ---
       |                     `-------------------'               ^
                           .----------o---------o------.         |
                        .--|--.       .--|--.       .--|--.
                        |     |       |     |       |     |
                        |     |       |     |       |     |
                        `-----'       `-----'       `-----'
 
                                               Zr is into the page.
 
 
   HGA Point and Center Locations Data
   -----------------------------------
 
      Relative positions of HGA gimbal points computed from [1] and
      center set based on [2] are:
 
         ----------------------------------------------------------------------
         Link#        X, m      Y, m      Z, m    CENTER/REF_FRAME
         ---------- --------- --------- --------- -----------------------------
         HGA_AZ     -0.272363 -0.387315 -0.307797 ROVER/ROVER
         HGA_EL      0.000006 -0.002316 -0.000043 HGA_AZ/HGA_AZ
         HGA         0.21      0.0       0.0      HGA_EL/HGA_EL

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.1.0 -- October 11, 2012 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.

--------------------------------------------------------

positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.

MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.

--------------------------------------------------------

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.
 
 
Version and Date
--------------------------------------------------------
 
Version 1.0 -- Thu Jul 31 17:34:12 UTC 2014
 
 
Contact Information
--------------------------------------------------------
 
If you have any questions regarding this SPK file, contact:
 
Boris Semenov, NAIF, x4-8136, Boris.Semenov@jpl.nasa.gov
 
 
Appendix 1: MKSPK Setup Files
--------------------------------------------------------

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.
 
 
Version and Date
--------------------------------------------------------
 
Version 1.0 -- Thu Dec  4 14:57:37 UTC 2014
 
 
Contact Information
--------------------------------------------------------
 
If you have any questions regarding this SPK file, contact:
 
Boris Semenov, NAIF, x4-8136, Boris.Semenov@jpl.nasa.gov

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.
 
 
Version and Date
--------------------------------------------------------
 
Version 1.0 -- Mon Mar 16 09:29:53 UTC 2015

--------------------------------------------------------

Boris Semenov, NAIF, x4-8136, Boris.Semenov@jpl.nasa.gov

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.
 
 
Version and Date
--------------------------------------------------------
 
Version 1.0 -- Thu Dec  3 21:02:30 UTC 2015
 
 
Contact Information
--------------------------------------------------------
 
If you have any questions regarding this SPK file, contact:
 
Boris Semenov, NAIF, x4-8136, Boris.Semenov@jpl.nasa.gov

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.

--------------------------------------------------------

Boris Semenov, NAIF, x4-8136, Boris.Semenov@jpl.nasa.gov

********************************************************************************
 
 
MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.
 
 
Version and Date
--------------------------------------------------------
 
Version 1.0 -- Thu Jul 28 17:22:59 UTC 2016

--------------------------------------------------------

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.
 
 
Version and Date
--------------------------------------------------------
 
Version 1.0 -- Mon Dec  5 17:58:11 UTC 2016

--------------------------------------------------------

Boris Semenov, NAIF, x4-8136, Boris.Semenov@jpl.nasa.gov

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.
 
 
Pedigree
--------------------------------------------------------
 
This file has been generated by ``msl_rover_pos2spk.pl'' script,
(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.

--------------------------------------------------------

MSL Reconstructed Surface Position SPK
===============================================================================
 
This SPK file contains reconstructed MSL position w.r.t. to sites and
positions of sites w.r.t. the landing site.

--------------------------------------------------------

(Ver. 1.2.0 -- July 29, 2013 -- BVS/NAIF, SCK/NAIF.) that ran the
MKSPK program to make rover and sites position segments.
